NPM-RESTART(1)                                                                                                                                                    NPM-RESTART(1)

NNAAMMEE
       nnppmm--rreessttaarrtt - Restart a package

   SSyynnooppssiiss
         npm restart [-- <args>]

   DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       This restarts a package.

       This runs a package's "stop", "restart", and "start" scripts, and associated pre- and post- scripts, in the order given below:

       1. prerestart

       2. prestop

       3. stop

       4. poststop

       5. restart

       6. prestart

       7. start

       8. poststart

       9. postrestart

   NNoottee
       Note that the "restart" script is run iinn aaddddiittiioonn ttoo the "stop" and "start" scripts, not instead of them.

       This is the behavior as of nnppmm major version 2.  A change in this behavior will be accompanied by an increase in major version number

   SSeeee AAllssoo
       • npm help run-script

       • npm help scripts

       • npm help test

       • npm help start

       • npm help stop

       • npm help restart

                                                                                  January 2021                                                                    NPM-RESTART(1)
